Node.Notes: Usually hostile encircling in sense of lay siege to. Here probably surround in a benevolent, protective sense.
Uncertain. Word usually means "to bruise." Many change word slightly to get "to hide" (supported by LXX). Some trace to semitic root meaning "to grip hard."
Uncertain. Seems to be "fearful things/fearfully I am wonderful." Many take as "I am fearfully and wonderfully made," in the sense of being so wonderfully and mysteriously made.
Uncertain. Some think "the depths of the earth" refer to Sheol. Most think it is a figure for the mother's womb.
Uncertain. The Qere "for it [there was] one among them" is problematic. Most follow the Kethiv "not": there was none of them.
Uncertain. Many think this word does not fit and substitute with "to come to an end," in the sense that "if I should finish counting Yahweh's thoughts.

Uncertain. Text seems to read "they take up in vain your cities" (also how LXX and Syriac interpret the text). Most read the word "your cities" as Aramaic for "your enemies" and see something like "your enemies take up [your name] in vain."
